description: UTI Mutual Fund - UTI-Gold Exchange Traded Fund is an exchange traded fund co-launched by Bank of Baroda, Punjab National Bank, Life Insurance Corporation of India, and State Bank of India. The fund is managed by UTI Asset Management Company (P) Ltd. It invests in the commodity markets. The fund invests in gold. It seeks to track the price of Gold. UTI Mutual Fund - UTI-Gold Exchange Traded Fund was formed on April 17, 2007 and is domiciled in India.
name: UTI Mutual Fund - UTI-Gold Exchange Traded Fund
